detail_description: Upvan Lake, located in Thane, Maharashtra, is an artificial and eco-friendly lake constructed by the Thane Municipal Corporation in 1880. It was later reconstructed to supply water to the Raymond Factory. The lake is renowned for its scenic beauty and hosts the annual Sanskruti Arts Festival. Nestled against the backdrop of Yeoor Hills, it offers a picturesque setting for picnics and leisurely strolls.
name: Upvan Lake
address: Thane West, Thane, Maharashtra

detail_description: The Thane Creek Flamingo Sanctuary, also known as the Airoli Flamingo Sanctuary, is a popular destination in Navi Mumbai. Spanning 50 acres, it features informative museums and a stunning flamingo point where visitors can observe thousands of migratory birds in their natural surroundings. Surrounded by mangrove forests, the sanctuary is home to various colorful bird species year-round, with the highlight being the arrival of pink-feathered flamingos during spring.
name: Thane Creek Flamingo Sanctuary
address: Mangrove forest, Coastal marine Biodiversity center, Airoli Creek, Diva Nagar Rd, Thane, Maharashtra 400708, India

detail_description: Yeoor Hills, situated near Thane and just 40 km from Mumbai, is a beloved tourist spot known for its picturesque forested hills, six charming villages, and a variety of rental bungalows. name: Yeoor Hills

excerpt: Sprawling, forested park home to the ancient Kanheri Caves, a lion & tiger safari & nature trails.
detail_description: Sanjay Gandhi National Park, formerly known as Borivali National Park, is a sprawling forested park located in Mumbai. It is one of the largest and most popular nature reserves in India. The park is home to a diverse range of flora and fauna, including tigers and leopards. Visitors can explore the ancient Kanheri Caves within the park, which are Buddhist cave temples dating back to the first century BC.
name: Sanjay Gandhi National Park
address: Mumbai, Maharashtra, India

detail_description: NaMo Grand Central Park in Thane is the first central park and one of the largest urban parks, covering 20 acres. It offers various play zones, beautifully designed gardens, a scenic lake area with fountains, and a viewing deck called X-bridge. The entry fee is Rs. 20 on weekdays and Rs. 30 on weekends for adults, while children under 15 enter for free. Plastic bottles are strictly prohibited inside the park, but there are water stations available.

excerpt: Thane is a city just outside Mumbai, in the western Indian state of Maharashtra. Its known as the City of Lakes, and its more than 30 lakes include tree-lined Upvan Lake, a popular recreational spot. Beside Talao Pali Lake, Kopineshwar Mandir is an old, domed Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Shiva. To the west, leopards, monkeys and parakeets inhabit the teak forest and bamboo groves of Sanjay Gandhi National Park.
detail_description: Thane, located just outside Mumbai in Maharashtra, India, is often referred to as the 'City of Lakes' due to its abundance of over 30 lakes. Upvan Lake is a popular recreational spot with its tree-lined shores, while Talao Pali Lake is home to the ancient Kopineshwar Mandir, a domed Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Shiva.
name: Thane
address: Maharashtra, India
